SUMMARY OF PERMISSIONS AND RESTRICTIONS
(For convenience only — the AGPL-3.0 license text is authoritative)
================================================================================

PERMITTED USES
--------------

• Use the software privately or internally
  - Permitted: YES
  - Conditions: May be used for any private, internal, or non-distributed purpose.

• Modify the source code for your own use
  - Permitted: YES
  - Conditions: No restrictions as long as changes remain private/internal.

• Share or distribute unmodified versions
  - Permitted: YES
  - Conditions: Must include the full AGPL-3.0 license text and complete source.

• Distribute modified versions
  - Permitted: YES
  - Conditions: Must release full source code under AGPL-3.0.

• Provide the software as a service (SaaS / network use)
  - Permitted: YES
  - Conditions: Users interacting over a network must be able to obtain the
    complete corresponding source code for the running version.

• Keep modifications private (no distribution or SaaS)
  - Permitted: YES
  - Conditions: Source disclosure is not required unless distributing or
    providing network access.

PROHIBITED USES
---------------

• Creating a closed-source or proprietary fork
  - Permitted: NO
  - Reason: All distributed or network-hosted modifications require source
    disclosure under AGPL-3.0.

• Hiding modifications behind paywalls, logins, or closed binaries
  - Permitted: NO
  - Reason: Source must be accessible to all users interacting with the software.

• Sub-licensing under a more restrictive or proprietary license
  - Permitted: NO
  - Reason: AGPL-3.0 copyleft restrictions must remain intact.

• Offering hosted or online access without sharing source
  - Permitted: NO
  - Reason: Network users must receive the source for the exact version in use.

================================================================================
COMMERCIAL / PROPRIETARY LICENSING
================================================================================

Need any of the following?

• Commercial use without copyleft obligations
• Proprietary or closed-source usage
• SaaS or hosted deployment without source disclosure
• Embedded or internal distribution without attribution

Commercial licenses are available.

These licenses waive AGPL-3.0 copyleft requirements, including:
- No obligation to publish source code
- No public attribution requirements
- SaaS, hosted, and embedded use allowed

HOW TO OBTAIN A COMMERCIAL LICENSE
----------------------------------

Open a GitHub Issue in this project’s repository to contact the maintainers
for licensing and pricing details.

We do not publish a direct email address to reduce spam.
Public GitHub contact is preferred and is actively monitored.
